<DOC><DOCNO> AP890602-0150 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-02-89 1614EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--BaldImmigrants     06-02 0128</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Bald Immigrants,0132</SECOND><HEAD>Indonesian Illegal Immigrants Shaved Bald to Prevent Return</HEAD><DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Immigration officials are shavingthe heads of illegal immigrants from Indonesia before they aredeported so they can be identified if they return immediately, anewspaper reported Friday.   There are about 1 million illegal immigrants from Indonesiaworking on plantations and construction sites in Malaysia,according to the government. Immigration officials arrest anddeport many of the Indonesians, but many return within a few days.   The New Straits Times daily on Friday quoted the ImmigrationDepartment in Batu Pahat, about 120 miles south of Kuala Lumpur, assaying officials have begun shaving deportees' heads.   The first group, 30 men, was deported by boat from Batu Pahat onWednesday, the newspaper said.</TEXT></DOC>